{
  "title": "ionic cordova resources",
  "body": [
    "div",
    null,
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Generate perfectly sized icons and splash screens from PNG source images for your Cordova platforms with this command."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "The source image for icons should ideally be at least ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "1024×1024px"
      ],
      " and located at ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "resources/icon.png"
      ],
      ". The source image for splash screens should ideally be at least ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "2732×2732px"
      ],
      " and located at ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "resources/splash.png"
      ],
      ". If you used ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic start"
      ],
      ", there should already be default Ionic resources in the ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "resources/"
      ],
      " directory, which you can overwrite."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "You can also generate platform-specific icons and splash screens by placing them in the respective ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "resources/<platform>/"
      ],
      " directory. For example, to generate an icon for Android, place your image at ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "resources/android/icon.png"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "For best results, the splash screen's artwork should roughly fit within a square (",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "1200×1200px"
      ],
      ") at the center of the image. You can use ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://code.ionicframework.com/resources/splash.psd"
          },
          "https://code.ionicframework.com/resources/splash.psd"
        ]
      ],
      " as a template for your splash screen."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic cordova resources"
      ],
      " will automatically update your ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "config.xml"
      ],
      " to reflect the changes in the generated images, which Cordova then configures."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "This command uses the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "cordova-res"
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://github.com/ionic-team/cordova-res"
        },
        "utility"
      ],
      " to generate resources locally."
    ],
    " ",
